definition: to cross/to go over/to pass (time)/to celebrate (a holiday)/to live/to get along/excessively/too-
to just scrape through with a narrow pass (in an exam)
(of birds) to migrate south for the winter

sentences.english: And the fairy mistress of dreams is coming towards you, flying through the twilight sky.
sentences.chinese: 仙鄉里的夢婆飛過朦朧的天空，向你飛來。

sentences.english: Is the sky in memory of Feiyan, flew over, they left off.
sentences.chinese: 記憶是天空中的飛雁，飛過，便留下過。

sentences.english: My parents used to live in South America and i used to fly there from Europe in the holidays.
sentences.chinese: 我的父母住在美國南部而我常在假期從歐洲飛過去。

sentences.english: They ducked down behind a wall as stones began to fly.
sentences.chinese: 他們在石塊飛過來時急忙俯身蹲到一堵牆後。

sentences.english: Mother looked, woodpeckers physicians see small tits fly over.
sentences.chinese: 循聲望去，啄木鳥醫師看到是小山雀飛過來了。

sentences.english: Some wild geese have just flown over.
An airplane flew across the sky trailing white vapor .
sentences.chinese: 一架飛機從空中飛過，尾部拖着一條水汽形成的白線。

sentences.english: A hundred planes will fly by the castle as a mark of respect.
sentences.chinese: 100架飛機將飛過城堡以示敬意。

sentences.english: Thoughts pass in my mind like swallows of lucks in the sky.
sentences.chinese: 思想掠過我的心上，有如一羣野燕飛過天空。

sentences.english: The number of flowers fluttering butterflies fly.
sentences.chinese: 飄飄的彩蝶飛過多少花。

sentences.english: Cards that fly all over the table, spill onto the floor, and disappear beneath a laser beam.
sentences.chinese: 卡片飛過桌子，落在地板上，消失在激光束下。

sentences.english: At that moment, the Jade Emperor flew past on a turbulent cloud, waving his arms.
sentences.chinese: 在那時，玉皇大帝揮舞著雙手，乘著一片亂雲飛過。

sentences.english: Many a winter's night she flies through the streets of the town, and peeps in at the windows;
sentences.chinese: 她常常在冬夜飛過城市的街道，朝窗子裏面望。

sentences.english: An arrow whizzed past his head.
sentences.chinese: 一支箭在他頭旁颼地飛過。

sentences.english: Two green-and-white butterflies fluttered past them.
sentences.chinese: 兩隻藍白色的蝴蝶從他們身邊飛過。
